"""A deliberately mis-formatted but lint-clean Starlark file.

buildifier --mode=check flags this file as needing formatting (the
`x+y` on the last line is reformatted to `x + y`), but it is otherwise
lint-clean: it has a module docstring, the function has a docstring, and
there are no unused variables or no-effect expressions. It exercises the
declarative check's *format* invocation end-to-end (one format finding,
zero lint findings), complementing malformed.bzl.fixture which is
format-clean but carries three lint warnings.
"""

def add(x, y):
    """Returns the sum of x and y."""
    return x+y
